### PriceWise API — click "Send Request" above each block (REST Client extension).
### Start the API first (VS Code task "Backend: run API" or: uvicorn app.main:app --reload).

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000

### 1. Health — is it alive?
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### 2. Readiness — DB + cache + catalog
GET {{baseUrl}}/ready

### 3. Parse a natural-language query
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/parse
Content-Type: application/json

{ "query": "phone with great camera under 50000, good battery, not Apple, for photography" }

### 4. Match products to a requirement
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/match
Content-Type: application/json

{ "requirement": { "category": "smartphone", "budget_max": 70000, "priorities": ["camera"] }, "limit": 5 }

### 5. Price check — fake-discount detection (note inflated iPhone MRP)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/price-check
Content-Type: application/json

{ "product_id": "iphone16pro", "urgency": "can_wait" }

### 6. Review trust — fake-review detection
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/review-check
Content-Type: application/json

{ "product_id": "s24ultra" }

### 7. Chat — multi-agent orchestration (capture session_id for the next call)
# @name chat1
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat
Content-Type: application/json

{ "query": "good camera phone under 70000 for photography" }

### 8. Chat — RESUME the same session (uses session_id from the call above)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat
Content-Type: application/json

{ "query": "what about battery life?", "session_id": "{{chat1.response.body.session_id}}" }

### 9. Discover — live data provider (mock by default)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/discover
Content-Type: application/json

{ "query": "oneplus", "category": "smartphone", "limit": 5 }

###############################################################
### AUTH FLOW — register, then use the token for alerts
###############################################################

### 10. Register (captures access_token)
# @name register
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{ "email": "you@example.com", "password": "supersecret1", "full_name": "Test User" }

### 11. Who am I? (uses captured token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{register.response.body.access_token}}

### 12. Create a price-drop alert (UC-08)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/alerts
Authorization: Bearer {{register.response.body.access_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "product_id": "iphone16pro", "product_name": "iPhone 16 Pro", "target_price": 115000 }

### 13. List my alerts
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/alerts
Authorization: Bearer {{register.response.body.access_token}}
